e^{Pt}
P=\left( \begin{matrix} 0&1&0 \\ 0&0&1 \\ 0&1&0 \end{matrix} \right)
P
\chi_A(x)=x^3-x
P^3-P=0
P^3=P
P=P^3=P^5=\dots
P^2=P^4=P^6=\dots
 \begin{align} e^{Pt}  &= I+Pt + \frac{P^2t^2}2 + \frac{P^3t^3}{3!} + \dots = \\ &= I + P\left(t+\frac{t^3}{3!}+\frac{t^5}{5!}+\dots\right) + P^2\left(\frac{t^2}2+\frac{t^4}{4!}+\frac{t^6}{6!}+\dots\right) = \\ &= I+ P \frac{e^t-e^{-t}}2 + P^2 \left(\frac{e^t+e^{-t}}2-1\right) = \\ &= I+ P\sinh t + P^2(\cosh t-1) \end{align} 
P=\begin{pmatrix}0&1&0\\0&0&1\\0&1&0\end{pmatrix}
P^2=\begin{pmatrix}0&0&1\\0&1&0\\0&0&1\end{pmatrix}
e^{Pt}= \begin{pmatrix} 1&\sinh t&\cosh t-1\\ 0&\cosh t&\sinh t\\ 0&\sinh t&\cosh t \end{pmatrix}.
